id: pm-ji5c
title: Pin CodeQL action refs to immutable SHAs in codeql.yml
description: "codeql.yml uses github/codeql-action/init@v3 and github/codeql-action/analyze@v3 (mutable floating tags) rather than SHA-pinned refs. Every other workflow (ci.yml, auto-release.yml, release.yml, nightly.yml) pins all actions to immutable SHAs per supply-chain security policy (pm-hfny was a closed issue that fixed the other workflows). codeql.yml was evidently missed."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 2
tags[3]: "area:ci",security,supply-chain
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:05:02.314Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-07T10:15:47.019Z"
author: audit-docs-tests-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- codeql.yml pins both github/codeql-action/init and github/codeql-action/analyze to the current immutable SHA for @v3\n- ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts PINNED_ACTIONS check extended to cover CodeQL actions (or a comment explains why it is excluded)"
parent: pm-u9d0
risk: medium
confidence: high
body: "## Context\n.github/workflows/codeql.yml lines 39 and 44:\n```yaml\nuses: github/codeql-action/init@v3\nuses: github/codeql-action/analyze@v3\n```\n\nAll other workflows use SHA-pinned refs (e.g. actions/checkout@de0fac2e... # v6). The CodeQL actions are run on push, PR, and weekly schedule, so this is an active attack surface.\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- codeql.yml pins both github/codeql-action/init and github/codeql-action/analyze to the current immutable SHA for @v3\n- ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts PINNED_ACTIONS check extended to cover CodeQL actions (or a comment explains why it is excluded)\n\n## Evidence\n.github/workflows/codeql.yml lines 39, 44; ci-workflow-contract.spec.ts PINNED_ACTIONS object (lines 17-25) does not include codeql entries"
